Studio"></div></div></div><h2 class=t-s-l2>The 'Mixing Secrets' Free Multitrack Download Library</h2><div class=s-hugo-content><p>To support readers of my book <span class=l-nowrap><a href=/ms/main/><i>Mixing Secrets For The Small Studio</i></a></span>, as well as music-technology students/educators in general, here&rsquo;s a list of multitrack projects which can be freely downloaded for mixing practice purposes. All these projects are presented as ZIP archives containing uncompressed WAV files (24-bit or 16-bit resolution and 44.1kHz sample rate). For maximum mixdown flexibility, the contributors have made every effort to provide audio &lsquo;raw&rsquo;, in other words without additional effects or processing (beyond treatments printed during tracking/editing). When importing the tracks, just make sure all the files start at exactly the same moment in time within your DAW&rsquo;s timeline. (<a href=/ms/mtk-faq>Download problems?</a>) In addition to the Full Multitrack packages, there are also many quick-download Edited Excerpt versions (usually featuring the song&rsquo;s biggest chorus) which provide &lsquo;bite-sized&rsquo; mixing assignments well-suited to classroom use. In both cases a preview mix is provided for easy auditioning while browsing through the list. If you&rsquo;re new to mixing, you can find some beginner-friendly projects on
my dedicated <a href=/ms/mtk-newbies>Suggestions For Newbies</a> page. <strong>If you&rsquo;d like to search for projects with specific instruments, track counts, download sizes, or Discussion Zone thread counts, then check out the new beta-version <a href=https://multitracksearch.cambridge-mt.com/ms-mtk-search.htm>library search page</a>.</strong></p><p>As well as the multitracks hosted directly on this site, I&rsquo;ve also included links to a few other decent downloads I&rsquo;ve discovered on other sites. If you have any projects of your own that you&rsquo;d be willing to post (or link to) here, then do get in touch. This is a continuously expanding resource, so if you want to keep track of the latest uploads please subscribe to my monthly spam-free &lsquo;Small-studio Secrets News&rsquo; mailing list &ndash; I usually post towards the end of the month. Many thanks to the artists and engineers who have kindly agreed to provide these files &ndash; please follow the links and check out their latest music!</p><p>All downloads from this site are provided free of charge for educational purposes only, and the material contained in them should not be used for any commercial purpose without the express permission of the copyright holders.
For projects hosted on other sites, please refer to their separate conditions of use. <strong>For more specific information on using the contents of this library in portfolios, research, publicity, competitions, teaching materials, etc. please refer to the <a href=/ms/mtk-faq>usage FAQs</a>.</strong></p><p><div class="m-advert m-advert--banner"><a href=https://audiomixclub.com/><img class=m-advert__image src=https://pix.cambridge-mt.com/Ads/PatronBanner_AudioMixClub.jpg alt="Audio Mix Club: Learn To Mix Online!"></a></div><div class="m-advert m-advert--banner"><a href=https://tourna-mix.com/><img class=m-advert__image src=https://pix.cambridge-mt.com/Ads/TournaMixAdJPEG.jpg alt="Tourna-Mix: The Ultimate Mix Competition Website"></a></div></p></div><div id=topAnchor></div><a href=#topAnchor class="l-link--white m-button m-button--primary m-button--back-to-top js-back-up-button">Back to
Top</a><div class=m-mtk-feature><div class="m-mtk-feature__pane m-mtk-feature__pane--side s-hugo-content m-mtk-feature__pane--side-left"><h3 id=span-class-m-mtk-track-new-flag-new-span-free-mixing-tips-podcast-series><span class=m-mtk-track__new-flag>NEW! </span>Free Mixing Tips Podcast Series!</h3><figure><a href=/mtkheroes><img src=https://pix.cambridge-mt.com/Ads/MtkHeroes_Banner_300x250.gif alt="New 6-part 'Multitrack Heroes' Pocast Series!"></a></figure><p>If you liked the <a href=https://www.soundonsound.com/techniques/three-ways-compress-snare-mike-senior-podcast>free <em>Sound On Sound</em> podcasts</a> I did a few months back, then check out my new six-part &lsquo;<span class=l-nowrap><a href=https://www.cambridge-mt.co.uk/mtk-heroes>Multitrack Heroes</a></span>&rsquo; series full of mixing tips specially for multitrack-library users. I explain what to listen for in each set of raw tracks, and share my own personal processing and effects tactics &ndash; with 200 audio examples to back it up!</p><h4 id=patron-video-tutorials>Patron
